cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image analysis and proposes a novel architecture for fusing multimodal data. It also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new architecture for deep learning and aims to improve the accuracy of automated diagnosis and prognosis. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with fusing information from multiple medical imaging modalities. 

Finally, neural networks (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new architecture for deep learning and involves training a neural network to classify polyps in endoscopy images.
